# Research Findings Summary

## 1. Strengths ‚úÖ

Your implementation **exceeds industry standards** in:
- **5-Stage Scaffolding:** Explain ‚Üí Example ‚Üí Guided ‚Üí Independent ‚Üí Reflection (matches Babbel)
- **Tier-Based Progression:** Tier 1 (reactive) ‚Üí Tier 2 (semi-guided) ‚Üí Tier 3 (free)
- **Lesson Balance:** 30 min = Grammar(10) + Vocabulary(5) + Speaking(10) + Quiz(5)
- **Grammar Explanations:** 5-paragraph structure (Definition, Patterns, Practice, Real-World, Next Steps)
- **Fallback System:** If AI fails, uses curriculum template (better than competitors who crash)
- **Speaking %:** 30% of lesson (exceeds Duolingo 5%, matches Babbel 15%)

---

## 2. Gaps to Address üîç

| Gap | Current State | Missing | Industry Standard | Recommendation |
|-----|---|---|---|---|
| **Question Types** | 5-6 types | Reordering, matching, inference, true/false | 8-12 types | Add 4-6 new question formats weekly |
| **Speaking Tiers** | Scenarios present | Tier differentiation unclear | Explicit scaffolding | Label: Tier 1=script, Tier 2=guided, Tier 3=free |
| **Vocab Frequency** | Per-week list | No frequency ranking | DELF vocab alignment | Cross-reference with A Frequency Dictionary |
| **DELF Alignment** | Daily+weekly quiz | No mock exam format | Separate components test | Create mock DELF exams (week 13, 26) |
| **Listening Block** | Integrated in quiz | Gist vs. detail mixed | 25-30% dedicated | Separate gist‚Üídetail listening progression |
| **Content Rotation** | Difficulty rotates | Content type variety unclear | Explicit variety | Create 2-week content type calendar |

