## 4. Confirmed Decisions (From Your Tarif)

‚úÖ **Structure:**
- 12 monthly files with daily lessons
- 52 weeks (day-counted, not calendar)
- A1‚ÜíA2 (levels), A2+ blocked

‚úÖ **Content:**
- Grammar: Static, explicit, teacher-created
- Examples: 50 per lesson (10 random)
- Quiz: 50 questions per lesson (content-identifier tagged)
- Vocabulary: Interactive, pseudo-random, bidirectional

‚úÖ **Features:**
- AI Chat: Stays (lesson level)
- Speaking: Scenario-based (lesson level)
- Homework: Backlog
- Progress UI: Visual bars (color-coded, week/month)
- Model: Busuu-style + dynamic + AI chat

---

## 5. Outstanding User Decisions Needed

### ‚ùì Decision 1: Peer Review?
- Option A: Community peer grading (Busuu model)
- Option B: AI-only scoring
- **Recommendation:** B (simpler to launch; can add A later)

### ‚ùì Decision 2: Gamification?
- Option A: Streaks, badges, XP (Duolingo)
- Option B: Progress bars only
- **Recommendation:** B (focus on content; can add A later)

### ‚ùì Decision 3: tu/vous Registration?
- Option A: Week 1 (both forms)
- Option B: Week 9 (A2.1 start)
- Option C: Week 13 (A2.2 start)
- **Recommendation:** B (DELF introduces formally at A2)

### ‚ùì Decision 4: Authentic Content?
- Option A: Week 9 (A2.1 boundary)
- Option B: Week 13 (A2.2 boundary)
- **Recommendation:** A (RFI/TV5 work at A2.1 level)

### ‚ùì Decision 5: Cultural Context?
- Option A: 1-2 notes per lesson
- Option B: One paragraph per lesson
- Option C: Minimal
- **Recommendation:** A (keeps lesson focused; Babbel model)

### ‚ùì Decision 6: Assessment Frequency OK?
- Current: Daily quiz + weekly exam + level exam
- **Question:** Too much? Ideal?
- **Recommendation:** ‚úÖ Optimal (Busuu = 3-4 lesson interval; you = daily option + weekly security)

